The acronym "RAT" stands for "Remote Access Toolkit," the previous article had it as "Remote Access Trojan," and although a remote access toolkit is a type of trojan virus, the acronym does not have the word trojan in it. The reason the acronym is NOT "Remote Access Trojan," is all Trojans can be remotely accessed, but not all trojans are classified as RATs, for example, a keylogger is a type of trojan, but it is not the same thing as a RAT.
